       title="Codecov Installation" id="Codecov-Installation">

    <primary-label ref="codecov"/>
    <secondary-label ref="codecov_version"/>
    <p>Installing the Codecov plugin is straightforward.</p>


    <chapter title="How to install Codecov" id="install">
        <p>To install the Codecov plugin, follow these steps:</p>

        <list type="decimal" start="1">
            <li><p>Open JetBrains IDE
            </p>
                <list type="bullet">
                    <li>
                        <p>Launch your JetBrains IDE and navigate to the
                            <ui-path>Plugins</ui-path>
                            section.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </list>
            </li>
            <li><p>Search for Codecov Plugin
            </p>
                <list type="bullet">
                    <li>
                        <p>Under the <ui-path>Marketplace</ui-path> tab, type
                            <ui-path>Codecov</ui-path>
                            and click the
                            <ui-path>Install</ui-path>
                            button.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li><p>Wait for the installation to complete and restart your IDE when prompted.</p>
                    </li>
                </list>
            </li>
        </list>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Sign in to Codecov with a personal token" id="codecov-sign-in">
        <p>To view coverage from your Codecov account inside the IDE, sign in using your Codecov personal token and
            select your service provider.</p>
        <list type="decimal" start="1">
            <li>
                <p>Create or copy your personal token from Codecov:</p>
                <list type="bullet">
                    <li>
                        <p>Go to your Codecov account settings and generate a
                            <emphasis>Personal Access Token</emphasis>
                            (PAT).
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li><p>Ensure the token has access to the repositories you want to view in the IDE.</p></li>
                </list>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Open
                    <ui-path>Settings | Tools | Codecov</ui-path>
                    and configure the connection:
                </p>
                <list type="bullet">
                    <li><p>Select your <b>Service provider</b>: <code>GitHub</code>, <code>GitLab</code>, or <code>Bitbucket</code>.
                    </p></li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Paste your token into the <b>Token</b> field and click
                            <ui-path>Save</ui-path>
                            .
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>After provider and token are set, the
                            <ui-path>Test connection</ui-path>
                            button becomes enabled.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </list>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click
                    <ui-path>Test connection</ui-path>
                    :
                </p>
                <list type="bullet">
                    <li><p>On success, the plugin confirms it connected to Codecov and displays the detected <b>Codecov
                        repository</b> that matches your current project (for example: <code>owner/repo</code>).</p>
                    </li>
                    <li><p>If the test fails, verify the provider selection, the token, and your repository
                        permissions.</p></li>
                </list>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Once the connection test succeeds, the plugin will detect your current project repository and show
                    coverage for your working branch when available (or the repositoryâ€™s default branch when the current
                    branch has no data).</p>
            </li>
        </list>
        <note>
            <p>Your token is stored securely by the IDE, following JetBrains <a
                    href="https://plugins.jetbrains.com/docs/intellij/persisting-sensitive-data.html">guidelines</a>.
                You can sign out or replace the token at any time from
                <ui-path>Settings | Tools | Codecov</ui-path>
                .
            </p>
        </note>
    </chapter>
